Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) officers have this evening arrested businessman Muktar Rehemtulla Omar over the alleged importation and repackaging of expired baby diapers. The diapers were recovered at a go-down within Athi River, Machakos County on October 12 2018. ALSO READ:

Who cleared 4 tonnes of expired diapers for import? The businessman will be charged with at least three offences among them; sale of substandard baby Diapers branded EZEE, sale of EZEE baby diapers without a valid import standardization mark (IS-Mark) permit and applying importation standardization mark (IS-Mark) to EZEE baby diapers without a valid permit issued by the Kenya Bureau of Standards (KEBS). Muktar will be produced in court tomorrow.